Key Match Events: Germany defeated Bosnia and Herzegovina 2-1 on October 11, 2024.
Denis Undav scored two goals for Germany in the 30th and 36th minutes.
Edin Dzeko scored for Bosnia and Herzegovina in the 70th minute.
Joshua Kimmich received a red card in the 90+5th minute.
Pre-Game Insights: Germany aimed to secure a spot in the quarter-finals of the UEFA Nations League.
Germany had taken four points from their first six in League A Group 3, while Bosnia and Herzegovina were still searching for their first victory.
Germany's coach Julian Nagelsmann was managing a squad with several key players out due to injuries or retirement.
Bosnia and Herzegovina's coach Sergej Barbarez was dealing with a team struggling to avoid relegation.
Post-Match Reflections: Germany's victory moved them closer to the quarter-finals of the UEFA Nations League.
Bosnia and Herzegovina continued to struggle in the tournament, remaining winless.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Germany's away performance had been historically weak in the Nations League, with only one win in nine matches before this game.
Bosnia and Herzegovina had a three-game winning streak at home in the Nations League before this match.
